# homeserver OS — Project Context

## What This Is

NixOS-based community server OS. Two interfaces:
- **Admin Panel** (Python, port 8080): Server management for the admin. Part of the bootloader, must never break.
- **Global Stack** (Next.js, separate repo): Community workspace for members. Installable app.

## Architecture Decisions (confirmed)

- **Apps per community**: Each community gets its own app instances via NixOS containers (Phase 6, not yet implemented). Currently apps are global.
- **SSO**: Single Sign-On via Authelia OIDC (Phase 5, not yet implemented).
- **Storage**: 3-2-1 backup schema enforced. Detailed per-app/per-community usage tracking.
- **Multi-community**: Multiple communities on one server, each with own apps and data.
- **Container isolation**: systemd-nspawn containers per community (planned).

## Current State

- Bootloader: stable (Admin Panel, Tailscale, SSH, Watchdog)
- Admin Panel: Dashboard + Apps (install/uninstall) + System (updates/rollback/terminal)
- Apps: Jellyfin, Nextcloud, Ollama, Syncthing, Vaultwarden, Gitea, HedgeDoc defined as modules
- Go API: routes for apps, system, communities, users (partially implemented)
- Global Stack: NOT yet integrated (separate repo, runs on Vercel)

## Key Files

- modules/bootloader/admin-panel.py — Admin Panel (DO NOT break this)
- modules/bootloader/default.nix — Bootloader layer definition
- modules/apps/*.nix — App modules (one per app)
- /etc/homeserver/apps.nix — Runtime file: which apps are enabled (written by admin panel)
- /etc/homeserver/mounts.nix — Runtime file: extra disk mounts (planned)
- docs/ROADMAP.md — Full roadmap with all planning decisions
- docs/ARCHITECTURE.md — Technical architecture

## Conventions

- Admin Panel changes: Python, inline HTML/JS, single file. Keep it simple.
- NixOS modules: declarative, lib.mkIf cfg.enable pattern, data under /data/.
- Runtime config files go to /etc/homeserver/ (created by tmpfiles, writable).
- Runtime state files go to /var/lib/homeserver/ (version, configured marker).
- All network operations must call ensure_dns() first.
- All rebuilds use --impure flag (for /etc/homeserver/ imports).
- German user, English code/docs.
